<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id56980c04-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s523"><num value="523">§ 523.</num><heading> Enforcement authority</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Subject to guidelines approved by the Secretary, members of the Coast Guard, in the performance of official duties, may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id56980c05-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s523/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> carry a firearm; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id56980c06-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s523/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><chapeau> while at a facility (as defined in <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s70101">section 70101 of title 46</ref>)—</chapeau><subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id56980c07-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s523/2/A"><num value="A">(A)</num><content> make an arrest without warrant for any offense against the United States committed in their presence; and</content>
</subparagraph>
<subparagraph style="-uslm-lc:I13" class="indent2" id="id56980c08-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02" identifier="/us/usc/t14/s523/2/B"><num value="B">(B)</num><content> seize property as otherwise provided by law.</content>
</subparagraph>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id56980c09-2930-11f1-a4c1-c531e6569a02">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tII/s208/a">Pub. L. 111–281, title II, § 208(a)</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/2912">124 Stat. 2912</ref>, § 99; renumbered § 523, <ref href="/us/pl/115/282/tI/s105/b">Pub. L. 115–282, title I, § 105(b)</ref>, <date date="2018-12-04">Dec. 4, 2018</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/132/4200">132 Stat. 4200</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
